On July 24, 2018, the President signed into law several bills designating various United States Postal Service facilities with specific names. These include the Marvin Gaye Post Office in Los Angeles, California, the Lance Corporal Jordan S. Bastean Post Office in Pekin, Illinois, the U.S. Navy Seaman Dakota Kyle Rigsby Post Office in Palmyra, Virginia, the J. Elliott Williams Post Office Building in Fort Mill, South Carolina, the Tuskegee Airmen Post Office Building in New York, New York, the Mabel Lee Memorial Post Office in New York, New York, the Bloomingdale Veterans Memorial Post Office Building in Bloomingdale, Illinois, the Lance Corporal Thomas E. Rivers, Jr. Post Office Building in Birmingham, Alabama, the First Sergeant P. Andrew McKenna Jr. Post Office in Bristol, Rhode Island, the Maurice D. Hinchey Post Office Building in Saugerties, New York, and the Sergeant First Class Alwyn Crendall Cashe Post Office Building in Oviedo, Florida. Additionally, the President signed the "Northern Mariana Islands U.S. Workforce Act of 2018," which makes changes to the transitional worker program for the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands.